\displaystyle 1+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1\cdot 5}{3\cdot 7}+\frac{1\cdot 5\cdot 9}{3\cdot 7 \cdot 11}+...............+(-1)
\displaystyle 1+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1\cdot 5}{3\cdot 7}+\frac{1\cdot 5\cdot 9}{3\cdot 7 \cdot 11}+............... = (1+x)^n = 1+nx+\frac{n\cdot(n-1)\cdot x^2}{2!}+.........
\displaystyle nx = \frac{1}{3}
\displaystyle \frac{n\cdot(n-1)\cdot x^2}{2!} = \frac{1\cdot 5}{3\cdot 7}
\frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{7} + \frac{1}{11} + ...
